Imam al-Ghazali's Books
Al-Ghazali (1058-1111 CE), also known as Abu Hamid al-Ghazali or Imam al-Ghazali, was one of the most influential Muslim philosophers, theologians, jurists, and mystics. Here's a list of his major works:
Theological and Philosophical Works

Tahafut al-Falasifa (The Incoherence of the Philosophers)
Al-Iqtisad fi al-I'tiqad (The Middle Path in Theology)
Faysal al-Tafriqa (The Decisive Criterion for Distinguishing Islam from Clandestine Unbelief)
Al-Mustasfa min 'Ilm al-Usul (The Essentials of Islamic Legal Theory)
Mihakk al-Nazar fi al-Mantiq (The Touchstone of Reasoning in Logic)
Mi'yar al-'Ilm (The Standard Measure of Knowledge)
Maqasid al-Falasifa (The Aims of the Philosophers)
Al-Qistas al-Mustaqim (The Just Balance)

Sufism and Spirituality

Ihya' 'Ulum al-Din (The Revival of the Religious Sciences) - his magnum opus
Bidayat al-Hidaya (The Beginning of Guidance)
Kimiya-yi Sa'adat (The Alchemy of Happiness)
Mishkat al-Anwar (The Niche of Lights)
Minhaj al-'Abidin (The Path of the Worshipful Servants)
Al-Munqidh min al-Dalal (Deliverance from Error) - his spiritual autobiography
Ayyuha al-Walad (O Youth!)

Legal Works

Al-Wajiz fi Fiqh al-Imam al-Shafi'i (The Concise Book on Shafi'i Jurisprudence)
Al-Wasit fi al-Madhhab (The Medium Book in the Jurisprudential School)
Al-Basit (The Extensive Book)
Al-Mustasfa min 'Ilm al-Usul (The Purified Source of the Science of Jurisprudence Principles)

Ethical Works

Mizan al-'Amal (The Balance of Action)
Ihya' 'Ulum al-Din (contains extensive ethical teachings)
Bidayat al-Hidaya (Beginning of Guidance)

Other Works

Nasihat al-Muluk (Counsel for Kings)
Jawahir al-Qur'an (Jewels of the Qur'an)
Al-Madnun bihi 'ala ghayri Ahlihi (The Reserved for Those Who Are Worthy)
Al-Maqsad al-Asna fi Sharh Asma' Allah al-Husna (The Highest Aim in Explaining God's Beautiful Names)